.TH "NAVIGATOR.TAINTENABLED" "3JS" "August 25, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Navigator.taintEnabled \- Navigator: taintEnabled() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Navigator.taintEnabled()\f[B]\f[R] method always returns
\f[CR]false\f[R].
.PP
Tainting was a security method used by JavaScript 1.2.
It has long been removed; this method only stays for maintaining
compatibility with very old scripts.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
taintEnabled()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
Always returns \f[CR]false\f[R].
